61.   Who is the governor of your state now? * 

• Answers will vary. [District of Columbia residents should answer that D.C. does not have a governor.]

62.   What is the capital of your state? 

• Answers will vary. [District of Columbia residents should answer that D.C. is not a state and does not have a capital. 

Residents of U.S. territories should name the capital of the territory.]



63.   There are four amendments to the U.S. Constitution about who can vote. Describe one of them. 

• Citizens eighteen (18) and older (can vote). 

• You don’t have to pay (a poll tax) to vote. 

• Any citizen can vote. (Women and men can vote.) 

• A male citizen of any race (can vote).
